Rating: 3
Excellent bars! Chewy, and not as sweet as I was worried they would be. I used half milk chocolate and half semisweet chips. As written, the recipe wouldn't be too sweet at all, but still rich. Nice balance of coconut and chocolate. Might be good with pecans added. The crust does tend to fall off the bottom when you're eating them. They would be perfect with coffee! I made them for our neighbors as a thank-you for mowing our lawn for us, and they were very well received.

Rating: 3
